@n7trd 

> A current pain point in Flutter is that even for something as simple as creating a custom text box with native-looking text selection and toolbar behavior, you have to integrate material and cupertino widgets into your UI library. This also means dealing with additional complexities like theming.

`super_editor` provides `SuperTextField` which doesn't use any Material or Cupertino pieces. In fact, it doesn't even use `RenderEditable`. It might need some updates for your use-cases - not sure - but the Flutter community should definitely feel empowered to use that text field and completely avoid Material and Cupertino stuff.
